Photo dump 📸💩 (I’ve always hated that phrase but it’s quite funny with the emojis lol). I’ve been trying to get OUTSIDE these past few months, after spending the entire year of 2022 in “hermit mode”. I’ve been working on myself, therapy, healing trauma, and focusing on my spiritual awakening. I finally feel like the heaviest part is behind me. Although life will continue to give me contrast until the day I die, I have learned to utilize it for learning experience and growth. So to all of you out there going through a difficult time- just know that you can transmute the energy into your growth and expansion if you choose the perspective of positivity. Everything is always working out for you, even if you can’t see it right now. Trust the universe. Trust yourself. Because you ARE a piece of the universe itself. #inspiration #spirituality #healing

Having a bad day and needed a pick me up- hence the sexy red look. I find the color red to be very empowering. Utilizing fashion and beauty as tools to help you feel better when shit hits the fan is a great life hack. (At least I think so.) Meditating and slowing down is also key to not losing your mind. It’ll get better, the clouds will subside. This is only temporary. Ok, my pep talk to myself is over. Hope this helped someone else who may also be having a crappy day. Love you. 🥰 #baddayquotes #inspirational
